Gaining practical skills to work with microbes, doing research, growing and identifying microbes.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of the Practical Course of Microbiology and Virology is to provide basic knowledge in understanding microorganisms and in handling them safely. Various experiments have been chosen to help students learn to recognize fundamental similarities and differences among microorganisms. The approach is ecological, attempting to give the students the knowledge how to isolate, inspect, inoculate, incubate, identify and enumerate microorganisms.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  After the course students are expected to: - know how to work safely with different microbes and bacteriophages - have acquired the skills to use basic microbiological methods in different applications
